  "text": "The SpiderMonkey JavaScript source code parsing and compilation to bytecode chain consists of five main stages:\n\n## 1. Compilation Entry Points (js/src/frontend/BytecodeCompiler.h)\n\nThe main entry points are extern functions that initiate compilation:\n- `CompileGlobalScript()` - Compiles global scope JavaScript\n- `CompileEvalScript()` - Compiles eval() scripts\n- `CompileModule()` - Compiles ES6 modules\n- `CompileGlobalScriptToStencil()` - Creates a Stencil without instantiation\n- `CompileStandaloneFunction()` - Compiles function expressions\n\n## 2. Parser (js/src/frontend/Parser.h and Parser.cpp)\n\nThe Parser generates an Abstract Syntax Tree (AST) from JavaScript source text. Key components:\n\n- **Parser class hierarchy**: `Parser<ParseHandler, Unit>` is templated on:\n  - `ParseHandler`: Controls full parsing vs syntax-only parsing (FullParseHandler vs SyntaxParseHandler)\n  - `Unit`: Character type (char16_t or mozilla::Utf8Unit)\n\n- **Main parsing entry methods** (in Parser.cpp, lines 1776-1900+):\n  - `globalBody(GlobalSharedContext*)` - Parses global scope code\n  - `evalBody(EvalSharedContext*)` - Parses eval code \n  - `moduleBody(ModuleSharedContext*)` - Parses module code\n  - These methods parse the token stream and return ParseNode tree results\n\n- **Parser also contains**:\n  - TokenStream for lexical analysis\n  - ParseContext for scope tracking\n  - SharedContext for compilation state\n\n## 3. AST Node Types (js/src/frontend/ParseNode.h)\n\nParseNode.h defines all AST node types using a macro-based system:\n\n- Base node types: NullaryNode, UnaryNode, BinaryNode, TernaryNode, ListNode\n- Specialized nodes via `FOR_EACH_PARSE_NODE_KIND(F)` macro (lines 63-150+):\n  - FunctionNode - Function declarations/expressions\n  - ModuleNode - Module bodies\n  - CallNode - Function calls\n  - PropertyAccess/PropertyByValue - Property access\n  - ConditionalExpression - Ternary operators\n  - And many more statement and expression nodes\n\n## 4. Bytecode Emission (js/src/frontend/BytecodeEmitter.h and BytecodeEmitter.cpp)\n\nByteCodeEmitter traverses the AST and generates bytecode:\n\n- **Main class**: `BytecodeEmitter` in BytecodeEmitter.h (lines 1-200+)\n- **Main emission method**: `emitScript(ParseNode* body)` (BytecodeEmitter.cpp, line 2354)\n  - Sets script start offset\n  - Emits bytecode for the entire script/function body\n  - Handles prologue and main bytecode sections\n\n- **Supporting structures**:\n  - BytecodeSection (in BytecodeSection.h) - Stores the actual bytecode bytes as it's generated\n  - PerScriptData (in BytecodeSection.h) - Stores GC things referenced by bytecode\n  - EmitterScope - Manages scope bindings during emission\n  - JumpList - Tracks forward jumps that need patching\n\n## 5. Bytecode Compilation Flow\n\n1. **ScriptCompiler::compile()** (BytecodeCompiler.cpp, lines 954-1017):\n   - Creates ParseNode via parser->globalBody() or parser->evalBody()\n   - Calls BytecodeEmitter::emitScript(ParseNode*)\n   - Emits bytecode into intermediate representation\n\n2. **Stencil Representation** (js/src/frontend/Stencil.h):\n   - CompilationStencil stores the compilation result\n   - ExtensibleCompilationStencil is mutable during parsing\n   - Contains vectors of: ScriptStencil, ScopeStencil, RegExpStencil, BigIntStencil, etc.\n   - Bytecode is stored in ScriptStencil objects\n\n3. **Bytecode Definition** (js/src/vm/Opcodes.h):\n   - Defines `JSOp` enum with all bytecode instructions\n   - Instructions defined via `FOR_EACH_OPCODE(MACRO)` macro\n   - Each opcode has: opcode ID, token string, length, stack effects, operand format\n   - Examples: JSOp::Call, JSOp::GetName, JSOp::SetProp, JSOp::Return, etc.\n\n## 6. Final JSScript Output (js/src/vm/JSScript.h and JSScript.cpp)\n\n- **JSScript class** (line 1787) represents a compiled script\n- **Bytecode storage**:\n  - `code()` method (line 1844) returns `jsbytecode*` pointer to bytecode\n  - `immutableScriptData()` returns ImmutableScriptData containing bytecode\n  - `length()` returns bytecode length in bytes\n- **Creation methods**:\n  - `JSScript::Create()` - Creates empty script structure\n  - `JSScript::fromStencil()` - Creates script from CompilationStencil\n  - `JSScript::fullyInitFromStencil()` - Fully initializes script from stencil\n\n## Compilation Sequence Summary\n\nSource Text → Parser (tokens → AST ParseNodes) → BytecodeEmitter (AST → bytecode) → Stencil (intermediate representation) → JSScript (runtime executable bytecode)\n\nThe chain leverages separation of concerns: the Parser focuses on syntactic analysis producing AST nodes, the BytecodeEmitter traverses that AST and generates sequential bytecode instructions, and JSScript provides the final runtime representation with immutable bytecode and metadata."
}

